    "---\n",
    "## 2. Residual Connections: Mathematical Analysis of Gradient Flow\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.1 The Vanishing Gradient Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "In a deep network without residual connections, the gradient at layer $l$ is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial h_l} = \\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial h_L} \\prod_{k=l+1}^{L} \\frac{\\partial h_k}{\\partial h_{k-1}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "If $\\left\\|\\frac{\\partial h_k}{\\partial h_{k-1}}\\right\\| < 1$ for many layers (common with sigmoid activations),\n",
    "this product vanishes exponentially: $O(\\rho^{L-l})$ for $\\rho < 1$.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.2 How Skip Connections Solve the Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "With residual learning $h_l = F(h_{l-1}) + h_{l-1}$, the gradient becomes:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial h_l}{\\partial h_{l-1}} = \\frac{\\partial F}{\\partial h_{l-1}} + I$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The identity term $I$ guarantees a gradient highway — even if $\\frac{\\partial F}{\\partial h_{l-1}} \\to 0$,\n",
    "the gradient is at minimum $1$ (identity). This makes the gradient at any layer:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial h_l} = \\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial h_L} \\left(1 + \\sum_j \\prod_{k \\in \\text{paths}} \\frac{\\partial F_k}{\\partial h_{k-1}}\\right)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The network effectively becomes an **ensemble of paths** of different depths — short paths provide\n",
    "immediate gradient, while long paths provide rich representations.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.3 Implication for DCAM in Mask R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Our DCAM is inserted *before* the residual addition, ensuring:\n",
    "$$h_l = \\text{DCAM}(F(h_{l-1}), D) + h_{l-1}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The skip connection bypasses DCAM in the gradient path:\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial h_l}{\\partial h_{l-1}} = \\underbrace{\\frac{\\partial \\text{DCAM}(F, D)}{\\partial h_{l-1}}}_{\\text{DCAM+conv path}} + \\underbrace{I}_{\\text{skip highway}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This means DCAM failures (saturation, poor initialisation) are safely bypassed,\n",
    "and the model can learn to use DCAM adaptively."
   ]
  },
