    "---\n",
    "## 5. Backpropagation Through DCAM: Full Gradient Derivation\n",
    "\n",
    "### Complete gradient of the DCAM module\n",
    "\n",
    "Let $F \\in \\mathbb{R}^{B \\times C \\times H \\times W}$ be the input feature map and\n",
    "$D \\in \\mathbb{R}^{B \\times 1 \\times H \\times W}$ the density map. DCAM outputs:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$F' = F \\odot s(F, D)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $s(F, D) \\in \\mathbb{R}^{B \\times C}$ are the channel attention weights.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Step-by-step gradient derivation:**\n",
    "\n",
    "Given $\\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial F'_{b,c,h,w}} = g_{b,c,h,w}$ (upstream gradient):\n",
    "\n",
    "**1. Gradient wrt F:**\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial F_{b,c,h,w}} = g_{b,c,h,w} \\cdot s_{b,c}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This is elementwise multiplication by the attention weights — clean and simple.\n",
    "\n",
    "**2. Gradient wrt attention weights $s$:**\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial s_{b,c}} = \\sum_{h,w} g_{b,c,h,w} \\cdot F_{b,c,h,w}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**3. Through sigmoid (Jacobian of $\\sigma$):**\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial s_{b,c}}{\\partial u_{b,c}} = s_{b,c}(1 - s_{b,c})$$\n",
    "where $u = W_2 \\cdot \\text{ReLU}(W_1 \\cdot z)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "**4. Through linear layers $W_1, W_2$:**\n",
    "Standard linear layer backprop:\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial W_2} = \\delta^{(2)} \\cdot h^T, \\quad\n",
    "\\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial W_1} = \\delta^{(1)} \\cdot z^T$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $\\delta^{(2)} = \\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial s} \\odot s(1-s)$ and\n",
    "$\\delta^{(1)} = W_2^T \\delta^{(2)} \\odot \\mathbb{1}[h > 0]$ (ReLU mask).\n",
    "\n",
    "**5. Gradient wrt density input $D$:**\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial D} = \\frac{\\partial \\mathcal{L}}{\\partial z_D} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial z_D}{\\partial D}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $\\frac{\\partial z_D}{\\partial D_{b,1,h,w}} = \\frac{1}{HW}$ (from global average pooling).\n",
    "\n",
    "This gradient is non-zero, meaning the density map can itself be optimised end-to-end\n",
    "if we use a learnable density estimator upstream."
   ]
