    "---\n",
    "## 6. Information-Theoretic Analysis of GIoU\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.1 Why Smooth-L1 is Suboptimal for Box Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "Smooth-L1 loss treats the four box coordinates $(x_1, y_1, x_2, y_2)$ independently:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\mathcal{L}_{SL1} = \\sum_{i \\in \\{x_1,y_1,x_2,y_2\\}} \\text{smooth}_{L1}(p_i - g_i)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Problem:** Two predictions with the same Smooth-L1 loss can have very different IoU values.\n",
    "The coordinates are geometrically coupled (they define a box) but Smooth-L1 treats them as\n",
    "independent regression targets.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.2 IoU as the Correct Information Measure\n",
    "\n",
    "IoU $= |P \\cap G| / |P \\cup G|$ directly measures the overlap ratio — the actual\n",
    "quantity of interest for object localisation. It is:\n",
    "1. Scale-invariant (same IoU for large and small boxes at equal relative overlap)\n",
    "2. Rotation-invariant\n",
    "3. Invariant to coordinate system choice\n",
    "\n",
    "These properties make it the natural metric, so using it as a loss (1 - IoU) creates\n",
    "gradient alignment between the optimisation objective and the evaluation metric.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.3 GIoU Extension\n",
    "\n",
    "GIoU addresses IoU's zero-gradient problem: when $P \\cap G = \\emptyset$, $\\text{IoU} = 0$\n",
    "regardless of how far apart the boxes are — no learning signal.\n",
    "\n",
    "GIoU $= \\text{IoU} - \\frac{|C \\setminus (P \\cup G)|}{|C|}$ where $C$ is the smallest\n",
    "enclosing box. This term is negative when boxes don't overlap, providing a gradient that\n",
    "pushes boxes toward each other even without overlap.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Range:** GIoU $\\in [-1, 1]$, with $\\mathcal{L}_{GIoU} = 1 - \\text{GIoU} \\in [0, 2]$.\n",
    "At perfect overlap, $\\mathcal{L}_{GIoU} = 0$; at maximum non-overlap, $\\mathcal{L}_{GIoU} \\to 2$.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "## 7. Summary: Mathematical Contributions\n",
    "\n",
    "| Component | Mathematical Foundation | Why It Matters |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Focal Loss | Gradient suppression via $(1-p_t)^\\gamma$ | 20-10,000× noise reduction |\n",
    "| GIoU | Enclosing-box gradient when IoU=0 | Always-nonzero localisation signal |\n",
    "| Dice Loss | Pixel-level F1 optimisation | Inherent class-balance handling |\n",
    "| Skip Connections | Identity term in Jacobian | Prevents gradient vanishing |\n",
    "| Group Norm | Batch-size independent statistics | Stable training at batch=2 |\n",
    "| AdamW | Weight-decayed gradient update | Converges to flat minima |\n",
    "| DCAM | Density-conditioned channel recalibration | Inductive bias for dense scenes |\n",
    "| Cosine LR | Smooth LR decay to flat minimum | Avoids oscillation at convergence |"
   ]
  }
